RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: B B GUN BULLSEYE set the pace, showed the way from a trio of outer pressers around the turn, inched narrowly clear at the quarter pole, and held sway. ANSLIE'S GUMDROP broke through the gate pre-race, but remained in the grasps of the assistant starter, quickly reloaded without further incident, pressed the leader from the outside, then from between rivals around the turn, briefly failed to keep pace with that one entering the lane, and chased her home well. MY ROYAL PRINCESS raced forwardly four wide, pressed around the turn, but yielded leaving the quarter pole, gave way while hanging on her left lead, yet saved show from an inner rival at the wire. EASY ACES laid off of the pace two wide, tucked entering the turn, saved ground, sustained a rail chase to bid for show in the closing stages, but narrowly missed. SADIE'S PORT lacked speed in the three path around the turn, fanned to the seven path in upper stretch, and moved up willingly. BLESS D'SOUTH tracked from the two path, chased from the between horses nearing midstretch while giving way. HONEYSUCKLEDELIGHT broke a step slow while last away from the gates, rushed between horses to stalk three wide, but came under a stiff drive while among foes into the turn, and weakened turning for home. GRACE'S VISION took a mild brush from an inner rival in the early stages, and was outrun thereafter.
